  "id": "MGASA-2019-0355",
  "summary": "Updated evince packages fix security vulnerability",
  "details": "The updated packages fix a security vulnerability:\n\nThe tiff_document_render() and tiff_document_get_thumbnail() functions\nin the TIFF document backend in GNOME Evince through 3.32.0 did not handle\nerrors from TIFFReadRGBAImageOriented(), leading to uninitialized memory\nuse when processing certain TIFF image files. (CVE-2019-11459)\n",
